    {
      "id": "ieMm2CsUEj3MWqiRp55Lj",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 601.4283935997549,
      "y": 2387.8096560252825,
      "width": 1049.4450690749104,
      "height": 900,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#cdd6f4",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0p8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 996783203,
      "version": 1403,
      "versionNonce": 56307651,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780521312669,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "EXTRA\n\n1. Sun Microsystem:-\nSun Microsystems had created a programming language named\nJava\nSun’s main business was selling powerful, expensive computers\nthat ran the internet’s infrastructure \nSun was called the internet’s primary “arms dealer.”\n\n2. Netscape :- \nDominant browser of the era\n\n3. Java’s superpower :- \nWrite once, run anywhere ( Uses Java Virtual Machine to run\nand does not care where are you using  Windows, Mac, or Linux\n\n4. Sun microsystem and Netscape patnership\n\nIn 1995 ,the two giants of the early web  the biggest browser\nand the biggest internet-server company  joined forces.",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "EXTRA\n\n1. Sun Microsystem:-\nSun Microsystems had created a programming language named Java\nSun’s main business was selling powerful, expensive computers that ran the internet’s infrastructure \nSun was called the internet’s primary “arms dealer.”\n\n2. Netscape :- \nDominant browser of the era\n\n3. Java’s superpower :- \nWrite once, run anywhere ( Uses Java Virtual Machine to run and does not care where are you using  Windows, Mac, or Linux\n\n4. Sun microsystem and Netscape patnership\n\nIn 1995 ,the two giants of the early web  the biggest browser and the biggest internet-server company  joined forces.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BrSTFAODLIIoxLWtlwA6N",
